body.name: Humminbird AS GPS HS Precision GPS Receiver with Heading Sensor,
features: Compatible with the following models: all APEX (requires the AS GPS adapter), all SOLIX (requires AS GPS NMEA adapter), all HELIX 15/12/ 10/ 9/8, all HELIX 7 G2N, G3N and G4N, all MEGA 360 Imaging models, all AS 360 Imaging models, all ONIX Series*, 859ci HD Combo, 859ci HD DI Combo, 859ci HD XD Combo, 899ci HD SI Combo, 959ci HD Combo, 959ci HD DI Combo, 959ci HD XD Combo, 999ci HD SI Combo, 1159ci HD Combo, 1159ci HD DI Combo, 1159ci HD XD Combo, 1199ci HD SI Combo
Receiver dimensions: 3.25" diameter, 1.5" high and comes with 20' cable and has a 1"-14 thread count stem mountable with an optional antenna stem (antenna stem not included).
This receiver requires software 6.570 or higher in the compatible Humminbird Legacy products.
Note: SOLIX and ONIX Series require purchase of AS GPS NMEA cable for connection. APEX requires the AS GPS adapter
Note: this GPS receiver WILL NOT work with InterLink.
fast position fixes accurate within 2.5 meters
Provides more accurate position fixes than the industry standard GPS

body.description: The AS GPS HS is a precision GPS receiver with heading sensor provides fast position fixes with an accuracy within 2.5 meters. An internal compass also provides constant boat heading displayed on your Humminbird chart screen, even while sitting still. This heading sensor makes it easy to understand your boat’s direction in correlation to the GPS chart for precision boat control.

Whether it’s chasing the next trophy, or staying a step ahead of your competition, we build innovative technologies to shed new light on the world below, narrow your search and put an end to guesswork. All so you can accomplish what you came here to do. No wasted casts. No doubt.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Another very good Humminbird product
reviews.reviewText: Works as advertised. Installed up front with my Helix 12 SI. I now have a better gps signal and a stationary heading indicator. Follow the online video on how to program your Helix to use this external sensor in lieu of the internal sensor in the Helix head unit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars honest reviews only
reviews.reviewText: works as it should. i don't know what else to say about it

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2023
reviews.reviewText: fast shipping real humminbird product. As for as for me it paid for itself on first trip for what I wanted it to do. Its on my boat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great add on to my Helix unit.
reviews.reviewText: Works great with my Helix 7 on my trolling motor keeping my heading on point while I move direction with my trolling motor.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 30, 2014
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Improved accuracy at slow speed.
reviews.reviewText: This receiver is great for slow speed trolling and other slow speed use. For over 10 mph the receiver that comes with your unit works well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 21, 2013
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Makes navigating the chart simple
reviews.reviewText: I mounted this unit on the rear deck and turned on the Humminbird 798 hd si. All I can say is wow....Now the chart is easy to navigate, and I am certain as to which way the craft is heading. It's worth owning. An external antenna is the only way to go.Mounting is simple I secured mine to the rear deck behind my seat. Mounting is not critical, as the satellites are able to see the antenna from several hundred miles above you....It's not like they can't see over your shoulder.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I have this mounted on my Polaris Ranger for ice fishing and will purchase a 2nd for my aBoat. GPS accuracy and speed, heading sensor accuracy are all excellent and just what I was hoping for.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 14, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Heading features makes following a course easy!
reviews.reviewText: Bought this unit to increase the accuracy of my Solix 12 position information. Mounted it on a $25 Ram D VHF antenna mount (perfect thread match) about 18” in front of the motor on my bass boat. No interference problems. Am using it with the Solix Live Chart function to map the bottom of a historically significant bay in my area. Allows me to run parallel track with close spacing to insure full bottom coverage of my DI and SI collections.
Decided to buy this open box from Amazon and was very disappointed. Did not work at all and almost messed up both of my fish finders. Kept getting glitches on the screen and could not get a gps lock.
